Which colonies were known as the “Bread Colonies?”;The Middle Colonies had extremely rich soil and were called the Bread Colonies.
What was the Northwest Passage?;Europeans falsely believed there was a waterway through North America to the Pacific Ocean and called it the Northwest Passage.
Who explored North America and has a bay in New York named after him?;Henry Hudson explored North America. Hudson Bay is named after him.
What guaranteed colonists in New York rights?;The Charter of Liberties guaranteed citizens of New York certain rights.
Who founded Pennsylvania?;William Penn founded Pennsylvania. Pennsylvanians had religious freedom.
What was Pennsylvania known as because of its location among the colonies?;Pennsylvania became known as the Keystone State because it was in the middle of the Atlantic States.
